modules.description: Reads from and writes to files, establishes network connections, and executes CPU-bound tasks in a concurrent manner. It operates on file descriptors, sockets, and asynchronous channels, enabling non-blocking I/O and parallel execution. Use it to build high-performance network servers or process large datasets efficiently.

Provides event loop management and environment access for Eio applications. Operates on `Eio_unix.Stdenv.base` to interact with system resources like file systems and networks. Used to start an application by running a main function within a platform-appropriate event loop, ensuring proper resource handling and cleanup.
